      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 42 六二</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 42 六二</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六二：或益之，十朋之龜弗克違，永貞吉。王用享于帝，吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The second SIX, divided, shows parties adding to the stores of its subject ten pairs of tortoise shells whose oracles cannot be opposed. Let him persevere in being firm and correct, and there will be good fortune. Let the king, (having the virtues thus distinguished), employ them in presenting his offerings to God, and there will be good fortune.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="yijing-042-yi__alignment-004">
      <prop type="x-work-id">yijing</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">yijing-042-yi</prop>
